      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, it only really dawned on me in the last day or so. Of course, we can keep doing the analysis we do for things that happen to be shaders, but I suspect we\u0027re okay as-is. The place we really lose out is when an FP would previously be implemented as: \"My opt flags are based on my children\u0027s opt flags\". In the most extreme case:\n\n  uniform shader child;\n  half4 main(float2 xy) { return sample(child, xy); }\n\n... should implement const-for-const, and others, and defer everything to the child.",
      "parentUuid": "5e9dc5a5_65d6785e",
      "revId": "cca610a54d37fa1fabb6902cd1dad6d413b2c1c3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
